      "content": "Ah, my apologies for the goblin misstep! Let's get back to the serious business of the escrow account. The third party holding the money in an escrow account is typically an escrow agent or company, often a neutral party like a title company or an attorney. They act as the goblin guard, ensuring that all conditions of the house purchase are met before releasing the funds.\n\nThe decision to release the money is based on the fulfillment of specific conditions outlined in the purchase agreement. These conditions usually include things like the home inspection being satisfactory, the loan being approved and funded, and the buyer having secured their mortgage. Once all these conditions are met, the escrow agent will release the funds to the seller, and the deed to the house will be transferred to the buyer. It's a way to ensure that both parties are protected and that the transaction goes smoothly, without any goblin-like surprises.",
